icontrol

Annotation Type AutoGUIAnnotation


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Documented
public @interface AutoGUIAnnotation

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.String[] ParameterNames
      An array of Strings that name all parameters of the method.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      java.lang.String[] DefaultValues
      An array of Strings that are used as initial values when populating the table in the User Interface.
      java.lang.String DescriptionForUser
      This should be a short description for the user of the functionality implemented by the method.
      java.lang.String[] ToolTips
      An array of Strings specifying the ToolTips shown when the mouse hovers long enough over the parameter name in the Table.

    • Element Detail

      • ParameterNames

        public abstract java.lang.String[] ParameterNames
        An array of Strings that name all parameters of the method. These names are used in the GUI to populate the table. If a method takes no parameters, specify an empty String[] (that is to use ParameterNames = {}). Note that the number of Strings must equal the number of arguments the method requires.

      • DescriptionForUser

        public abstract java.lang.String DescriptionForUser
        This should be a short description for the user of the functionality implemented by the method. This Text will be displayed as ToolTip when the mouse hovers long enough over an item in the jCommandList.

        Use html-tags (see example above) to format the message nicely if you like. An empty String is allowed, and specifying the DescriptionForUser can be omitted because a default DescriptionForUser is specified in the declaration of AutoGUIAnnotation.

        Default:
        ""

      • DefaultValues

        public abstract java.lang.String[] DefaultValues
        An array of Strings that are used as initial values when populating the table in the User Interface. Not every parameter has to have a default value. The String must be formated in such a way that the constructor of the corresponding type (for instance Integer(), Boolean()) can convert the String, otherwise an error message is shown. Specifying an empty String is also allowed. Specifying the DefaultValues can be omitted because default DefaultValues is specified in the declaration of AutoGUIAnnotation.
        Default:
        {}

      • ToolTips

        public abstract java.lang.String[] ToolTips
        An array of Strings specifying the ToolTips shown when the mouse hovers long enough over the parameter name in the Table. Not every parameter needs a ToolTip, and empty ToolTips are also allowed. Specifying the ToolTips can be omitted because default ToolTips is specified in the declaration of AutoGUIAnnotation.
        Default:
        {}
